to the editor re peter stone award winning writer of '1776 dies at 73 obituary april 28 your obituary did n't mention an aspect of peter stone 's career that may prove to be his most significant and enduring legacy for 17 years peter served as president of the dramatists guild of america finding time in his hectic creative schedule he was a fearless and ferocious advocate for his fellow writers defending the interests of america 's playwrights composers and lyricists with a gusto uniquely his peter was a natural born politician who had a politician 's relish for the rough and tumble of confrontation negotiation and compromise but behind the pleasure he took in the advocacy process lay a profound commitment to the art form that is the american theater and to the authors who create it john weidman pres dramatists guild of america new york may 1 2003

